Finally, the HCHO measurement was conducted for underground water, tap water and wastewater samples (Table 3
                        ) to assess the feasibility of implementing the present chemosensor for real samples. All determination for real samples were carried out by means of the standard addition technique. The preparation of real samples was also performed following to the mentioned approach in the Section 2.4. Furthermore, certain amounts of HCHO standard solution were spiked in real samples and analyzed via standard addition technique to validate the offered method. The recoveries were in acceptable range which implied that the introduced chemosensor was applicable for determination of HCHO in real samples. For additional validity assessment, the obtained data for real samples were compared with a fluorimetric method [57] that exhibited a good accuracy of the employed chemosensor for HCHO determining in the real samples (Table 4
                        ).
